<br>
Example:  This weekend we took out Thaken Griften in WK with two clerics, two druids, an enchanter (for his epic), me a 50 pallie and a 47 beastlord.<br>
<br>
I really need to be able to step up for these occasions.  My first priority is leveling and I know that'll shore up my numbers quite a bit.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=343063">Viatanq</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I do best with goals though.  If I don't have a goal I fritter money away terribly.  I always have an enchanter for haste, and I just can't justify the kind of money I'd need to spend to get abother 10% haste.<br>
<br>
Judging by other people's advice, cloak of the Maelstorm is great for the back, but I'd only gain 20hp and 3 ac for 6k, that's not bad, but are there other improvements I could be making with a better bang for the buck?<br>
<br>
This is the order I'm thinking of:<br>
<br>
1) Still have a plat fire wedding ring that needs to be velium<br>
2) Death Mask of the Elysians or Gantru Warmask<br>
3) Idol of the thorned (Could still get exp camping this I think)<br>
4) Enchanted Dwarven Boots<br>
5) Brellium Wrists x 2<br>
6) Earring of the Solstace (once I hit 51)<br>
7) Stone Axe of Dismay ( again 51)<br>
8) Tae Ew War helm (once I hit 51) (Brellium Helmet?)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=401908">Viatanq Proposed Changes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Do you think my priorities are right?  What should I be saving up for?  What should be the big ticket big payoff goal peice? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umcdulldull.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdulldull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/30/02 8:14:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4046.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Workhorse</span><hr size=1> Sorry I am not writing to answer your exact questions but just some general advice.<br>
<br>
I would not recommend buying gears that can be obtained through velious armor quests such as helm, gauntlet, bracers, BP, leggings, shoulder and boots. Those can be obtained relatively easily. I think your guild is capable in doing Kael Arena and Manor (plate cycle). I actually tank in Kael arena when I was lvl52 (less than 1k ac fully buffed). The key class you need is a chanter/shammy who is able to land slow. I would say a lvl54+. Shammy &gt; Chanter.<br>
<br>
Obvious upgrades are: <br>
- 6AC 65HP rings<br>
-Idol of Thorn (I’d say Goranga idol, its almost free anyway)<br>
<br>
After all, Level &gt;&gt; ALL.<br>
